@startuml sequence_plugin_fire
' SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-SA-4.0
title PluginRegistry.fire() - scenari TRUSTED/SANDBOXED
participant "AssignmentService" as AS
participant "ActivityService" as ACS
participant "PluginRegistry" as PR
participant "PluginTrustRegistry" as TR
participant "StatusValidator\nTRUSTED" as SV
participant "NotifyOnCreate\nSANDBOXED" as SN

== BEFORE con abort TRUSTED ==
AS -> PR: fire(BEFORE_CREATE_ASSIGNMENT, ctx)
activate PR
PR -> TR: get_level("status-validator")
TR --> PR: TRUSTED
PR -> SV: execute(HookContext reale)
SV --> PR: ctx.abort=True,\nuser_message="Assegnazione non valida"
PR -> PR: interrompe il ciclo
PR --> AS: OperationAbortedError(user_message,\nabort_reason)
deactivate PR

== BEFORE SANDBOXED ignorato ==
AS -> PR: fire(BEFORE_CREATE_ASSIGNMENT, ctx)
activate PR
PR -> TR: get_level("notify-on-create")
TR --> PR: SANDBOXED
PR -> PR: crea ScopedHookContext\nsenza content/raw_content/file_bytes
PR -> SN: execute(scoped_context)
SN --> PR: abort=True,\nresult modificato
PR -> PR: log warning; ignora mutazioni sandbox
PR --> AS: HookContext reale invariato
deactivate PR

== AFTER con eccezione ==
ACS -> PR: fire(AFTER_UPDATE_STATUS, ctx con result=activity)
activate PR
PR -> TR: get_level("notify-on-create")
TR --> PR: SANDBOXED
PR -> SN: execute(scoped_context)
SN --> PR: Exception("timeout")
PR -> PR: log exception; continua
PR --> ACS: HookContext reale
deactivate PR
@enduml
